ions, project documents, and the agreement.", "optionB": "Yes, always.", "optionC": "No, never.", "optionD": "Only for commercial buildings.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0573", "question": "During a site visit, the sample flat contains premium fittings that are not included in the standard specification. The agent should:", "optionA": "Clearly explain which features are standard and which are optional.", "optionB": "State that every unit includes the premium fittings.", "optionC": "Avoid discussing specifications.", "optionD": "Tell the buyer to decide later.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0574", "question": "A promoter launches a \"limited period offer.\" Before advertising it, the agent should verify:", "optionA": "That the offer is genuine, documented, and consistent with project terms.", "optionB": "Only the discount amount.", "optionC": "Only the advertisement design.", "optionD": "Only the booking form.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0575", "question": "A buyer wants to purchase jointly with a family member. The agent should:", "optionA": "Ensure the transaction documents correctly reflect the proposed purchasers.", "optionB": "Register only one buyer.", "optionC": "Avoid joint ownership.", "optionD": "Leave the names blank.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0576", "question": "A promoter changes the project's contact details. The agent's best practice is to:", "optionA": "Update all future communications with the verified details.", "optionB": "Continue using the old details.", "optionC": "Ignore the change.", "optionD": "Wait for buyers to complain.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0577", "question": "A buyer asks for a copy of the sanctioned layout. The agent should:", "optionA": "Help the buyer obtain the officially available sanctioned plan where permissible.", "optionB": "Draw a sketch instead.", "optionC": "Refuse without explanation.", "optionD": "Show only marketing artwork.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0578", "question": "Which action best demonstrates fairness when multiple buyers want the same unit?", "optionA": "Follow a transparent allocation process consistent with applicable procedures.", "optionB": "Sell secretly to the highest bidder.", "optionC": "Give preference only to friends.", "optionD": "Delay informing other buyers.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0579", "question": "An agent notices that an online property listing contains outdated possession information. The agent should:", "optionA": "Correct or remove the inaccurate information promptly.", "optionB": "Leave it unchanged.", "optionC": "Wait until the booking.", "optionD": "Blame the website.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0580", "question": "A buyer asks whether a promised clubhouse will definitely be completed. The agent should:", "optionA": "Refer only to the approved project documents and official disclosures.", "optionB": "Guarantee completion.", "optionC": "Give a personal assurance.", "optionD": "Ignore the question.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0581", "question": "A professional agent should verify a buyer's identity primarily to:", "optionA": "Support proper documentation and transaction compliance.", "optionB": "Increase commission.", "optionC": "Estimate property value.", "optionD": "Avoid site visits.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0582", "question": "A promoter requests changes to a signed booking form. The agent should:", "optionA": "Ensure any changes are handled through proper documented procedures.", "optionB": "Edit the form without informing the buyer.", "optionC": "Ignore the buyer.", "optionD": "Replace the form secretly.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0583", "question": "If two project documents appear inconsistent, the agent should:", "optionA": "Seek clarification before advising the buyer.", "optionB": "Choose the shorter document.", "optionC": "Ignore the difference.", "optionD": "Use whichever is older.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0584", "question": "Which practice best protects an agent during future disputes?", "optionA": "Maintaining dated written records of important communications.", "optionB": "Depending only on phone conversations.", "optionC": "Avoiding emails.", "optionD": "Destroying old documents.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0585", "question": "A buyer requests clarification on additional charges. The agent should:", "optionA": "Explain each disclosed charge separately using available documents.", "optionB": "State that charges are confidential.", "optionC": "Guess the amount.", "optionD": "Discuss only the basic price.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0586", "question": "A real estate agent should immediately inform buyers if:", "optionA": "A material project update affects previously shared information.", "optionB": "Office furniture changes.", "optionC": "The agent changes a mobile phone.", "optionD": "Weather conditions change.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0587", "question": "A buyer wants to cancel after paying the booking amount. The agent should:", "optionA": "Explain that the consequences depend on the agreement and applicable law.", "optionB": "Guarantee a full refund.", "optionC": "Refuse to discuss cancellation.", "optionD": "Promise immediate repayment.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0588", "question": "Which action demonstrates impartial advice?", "optionA": "Presenting both advantages and limitations of a project honestly.", "optionB": "Hiding all disadvantages.", "optionC": "Promoting only high-commission projects.", "optionD": "Criticizing competitors without facts.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0589", "question": "Before arranging a booking, an agent should verify:", "optionA": "That the unit details and pricing match the current official information.", "optionB": "Only the buyer's occupation.", "optionC": "Only the office location.", "optionD": "Only the brochure cover.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0590", "question": "Which quality is most valuable when handling first-time homebuyers?", "optionA": "Patience and clear explanation.", "optionB": "High-pressure selling.", "optionC": "Technical jargon.", "optionD": "Aggressive negotiation.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0591", "question": "If a buyer asks whether a future road will definitely increase property value, the correct response is:", "optionA": "Future market values cannot be guaranteed.", "optionB": "Property values always double.", "optionC": "The increase is legally assured.", "optionD": "Appreciation is fixed under RERA.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0592", "question": "A promoter issues a revised payment milestone. The agent should:", "optionA": "Ensure buyers receive the updated official schedule before further transactions.", "optionB": "Continue using the previous schedule.", "optionC": "Ignore the revision.", "optionD": "Create a new schedule independently.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0593", "question": "A buyer notices a mismatch between the unit number in two documents. The agent should:", "optionA": "Resolve the discrepancy before proceeding.", "optionB": "Ignore the mismatch.", "optionC": "Change the number verbally.", "optionD": "Continue the booking.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0594", "question": "Which behaviour best demonstrates professional independence?", "optionA": "Advising clients based on verified facts rather than sales pressure.", "optionB": "Following every instruction without question.", "optionC": "Making unsupported claims.", "optionD": "Concealing material information.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0595", "question": "A real estate agent should avoid collecting:", "optionA": "Documents that are unrelated or unnecessary for the transaction.", "optionB": "Required KYC documents.", "optionC": "Buyer contact information needed for the transaction.", "optionD": "Signed application forms.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0596", "question": "If an allottee requests copies of important transaction documents after booking, the agent should:", "optionA": "Assist in providing or locating the documents that may properly be shared.", "optionB": "Refuse automatically.", "optionC": "Delay indefinitely.", "optionD": "Ask the buyer to search online without guidance.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0597", "question": "Which factor most improves an agent's professional credibility?", "optionA": "Consistent compliance with legal and ethical standards.", "optionB": "Expensive advertising.", "optionC": "A large office.", "optionD": "Social media popularity.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0598", "question": "Before recommending a property to an investor, an agent should:", "optionA": "Understand the investor's objectives while avoiding guarantees about future performance.", "optionB": "Promise fixed annual returns.", "optionC": "Guarantee resale value.", "optionD": "Predict future prices.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0599", "question": "The most effective way to reduce misunderstandings in property transactions is:", "optionA": "Accurate documentation supported by clear communication.", "optionB": "Oral promises.", "optionC": "Last-minute changes.", "optionD": "Informal agreements.", "answer": "A"}, {"qid": "Q0600", "question": "The hallmark of an excellent MahaRERA-certified real estate agent is:", "optionA": "Professional competence, ethical conduct, transparency, and compliance with applicable law.", "optionB": "Maximum commission.", "optionC": "Fastest sales only.", "optionD": "Aggressive marketing.", "answer": "A"}];

// Clears the Questions sheet (keeping the header row) and writes all
// 600 questions in a single batch write. Safe to re-run — it always
// starts from a clean slate so you never get duplicates.
function bulkImportQuestions() {
  const ss = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet();
  const sh = ss.getSheetByName("Questions");
  if (!sh) throw new Error('Run setupSheets() first — "Questions" sheet not found.');

  // Wipe existing data rows below the header
  const lastRow = sh.getLastRow();
  if (lastRow > 1) sh.getRange(2, 1, lastRow - 1, sh.getLastColumn()).clearContent();

  const rows = ALL_QUESTIONS.map(q => [
    q.qid, q.question, q.optionA, q.optionB, q.optionC, q.optionD, q.answer, 2
  ]);

  sh.getRange(2, 1, rows.length, 8).setValues(rows);
  SpreadsheetApp.flush();
  Logger.log("Imported " + rows.length + " questions into the Questions sheet.");
}
